data.content:
Your code **does not use `Thread.Abort`**, `Thread.Interrupt`, `ThreadAbortException`, or `Thread.ResetAbort`. It only uses `Thread.Start()`, `Thread.Join()`, and `Thread.Sleep()` — all of which work identically in .NET 8 with no migration needed.

That said, the code could be modernized to use `Task`/`Parallel` instead of raw threads:

```csharp
public void RunBatch(List<WorkItem> items)
{
    Parallel.ForEach(items, item => Process(item));
}
```

This gives you better thread pool usage and simpler code, but it's an **optional improvement**, not a required migration step. Your existing code will compile and run correctly on .NET 8 as-is.
